Define the extension of a fractional ideal along a ring homomorphism, and prove some basic facts about extensions.

This PR is part 2/4 of a proof of `isDedekindDomain_iff_isDedekindDomainDvr`.
Part 1: #14099
Part 3: #14237
Part 4: #14242

- [x] depends on: #14099

```suggestion
lemma coe_extended_eq_span : I.extended L hf = span B (map_f '' I) := by
```
This lets the coercion mechanism take over. 

Making this a `simp` theorem would make sense.

```suggestion
theorem extended_zero : extended L hf (0 : FractionalIdeal M K) = 0 := by
  apply coeToSubmodule_injective
  simp only [coe_extended_eq_span, coe_zero]
  have : ((0 : FractionalIdeal M K) : Set K) = {0} := by ext; simp
  simp [this]
```
I think all of these can be streamlined a bit by reducing immediately to a question about submodules. 

`convert` and `change`s should probably a tool of last resort. I think they can all be removed. 

This could also be made a `simp`.

```suggestion
  simp only [coe_extended_eq_span]
```
This can also be a `simp`.
